      "id": "a7a2bc4b84640673",
      "url": "https://lucijagregov.com/2017/02/26/regression-linear/",
      "title": "Linear Regression",
      "content_html": "\u003cp style=\"text-align:left;\"\u003eRegression models are most studied and best understood models in statistics. Regression and correlation are closely related and were invented by \u003ca href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Francis_Galton\"\u003eFrancis Galton\u003c/a\u003e, the famous Victorian statistician.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn linear regression, we model the relationship between two variables \u0026#8211; dependent and independent variable and we represent the data by drawing a line through it. Before fitting the data and deciding whether we are going to use linear regression or something else, we need to check whether there is a  relationship between variables. For this, a \u003ca href=\"http://www.stat.yale.edu/Courses/1997-98/101/scatter.htm\"\u003escatterplot\u003c/a\u003e can be helpful.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan id=\"more-939\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf a scatterplot doesn\u0026#8217;t show any decreasing or increasing of data, then fitting the linear regression to data will not be useful. To determine the association between the two variables and how well the model fits the observations, we use the \u003ca href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Correlation_coefficient\"\u003ecorrelation coefficient\u003c/a\u003e, which has values between \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=-1\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=-1\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=-1\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"-1\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e and \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=1\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=1\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=1\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"1\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e. We fit the data using ordinary least squares method.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMost machine learning algorithms can be divided into \u003ca href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supervised_learning\"\u003esupervised\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unsupervised_learning\"\u003eunsupervised\u003c/a\u003e learning. In supervised learning, we already know what our output should look like. We can categorize supervised learning further, into regression and classification problems.  In unsupervised learning, we have no knowledge of how our output should look like. I will talk about the machine learning methods for unsupervised learning later in this blog.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLinear regression is a form of a supervised learning algorithm where the output is a continuous function (a number), while in categorisation problems, the output is discrete.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLet\u0026#8217;s take a look at an example. Suppose we have a dataset with salary and years of experience columns in it (two variables where the \u0026#8220;salary\u0026#8221; is the dependent variable \u0026#8211; the one we are trying to predict and \u0026#8220;years of experience\u0026#8221; is the independent variable).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" data-attachment-id=\"1081\" data-permalink=\"https://lucijagregov.com/2017/02/26/regression-linear/screen-shot-2017-03-11-at-11-51-29/\" data-orig-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-11-at-11-51-29.png\" data-orig-size=\"328,402\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026quot;aperture\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;credit\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;camera\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;caption\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;created_timestamp\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;copyright\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;focal_length\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;iso\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;shutter_speed\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;title\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;orientation\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Screen Shot 2017-03-11 at 11.51.29\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-11-at-11-51-29.png?w=245\" data-large-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-11-at-11-51-29.png?w=328\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1081\" src=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-11-at-11-51-29.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2017-03-11 at 11.51.29\" width=\"328\" height=\"402\" srcset=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-11-at-11-51-29.png 328w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-11-at-11-51-29.png?w=122\u0026amp;h=150 122w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-11-at-11-51-29.png?w=245\u0026amp;h=300 245w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 328px) 100vw, 328px\" /\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSuppose the number of data points in the file is \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=n\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=n\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=n\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"n\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e, \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%28x_%7Bi%7D%2C+y_%7Bi%7D%29%2C+%C2%A0i+%3D+1%2C+%5Ccdots%2C+n\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%28x_%7Bi%7D%2C+y_%7Bi%7D%29%2C+%C2%A0i+%3D+1%2C+%5Ccdots%2C+n\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%28x_%7Bi%7D%2C+y_%7Bi%7D%29%2C+%C2%A0i+%3D+1%2C+%5Ccdots%2C+n\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"(x_{i}, y_{i}),  i = 1, \u0026#92;cdots, n\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e. The relation between the variables is then\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y_%7Bi%7D+%3D+b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7D%2Ax_%7Bi%7D+%2B+%5Cepsilon_%7Bi%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y_%7Bi%7D+%3D+b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7D%2Ax_%7Bi%7D+%2B+%5Cepsilon_%7Bi%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y_%7Bi%7D+%3D+b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7D%2Ax_%7Bi%7D+%2B+%5Cepsilon_%7Bi%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"y_{i} = b_{0} + b_{1}*x_{i} + \u0026#92;epsilon_{i}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand the goal is to find the  linear regression line\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y+%3D+b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7D+%2A+x\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y+%3D+b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7D+%2A+x\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y+%3D+b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7D+%2A+x\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"y = b_{0} + b_{1} * x\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e,\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eor in our case\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Salary+%3D+b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7D+%2A+Experience\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Salary+%3D+b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7D+%2A+Experience\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Salary+%3D+b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7D+%2A+Experience\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"Salary = b_{0} + b_{1} * Experience\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLeast squares is the method which calculates the best line to fit the data by minimizing the sum of the squares of distances from each point to the regression line. Since the distances are squared, we can be sure that we will get positive values and that there will be no cancellation between data points.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_1006\" style=\"width: 430px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"\u003e\u003cimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1006\" loading=\"lazy\" data-attachment-id=\"1006\" data-permalink=\"https://lucijagregov.com/2017/02/26/regression-linear/screen-shot-2017-02-26-at-12-30-12/\" data-orig-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-02-26-at-12-30-12.png\" data-orig-size=\"420,422\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026quot;aperture\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;credit\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;camera\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;caption\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;created_timestamp\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;copyright\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;focal_length\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;iso\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;shutter_speed\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;title\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;orientation\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;}\" data-image-title=\"screen-shot-2017-02-26-at-12-30-12\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-02-26-at-12-30-12.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-02-26-at-12-30-12.png?w=420\" class=\" size-full wp-image-1006 aligncenter\" src=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-02-26-at-12-30-12.png\" alt=\"screen-shot-2017-02-26-at-12-30-12\" width=\"420\" height=\"422\" srcset=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-02-26-at-12-30-12.png 420w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-02-26-at-12-30-12.png?w=150\u0026amp;h=150 150w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-02-26-at-12-30-12.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=300 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\" /\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-1006\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"\u003eFigure taken from http://mathworld.wolfram.com/LeastSquaresFitting.html\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn the figure above you can see what I mean by \u0026#8220;distance of data points from the regression line\u0026#8221;.  The least squares method is minimizing the following\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cmin+%5Climits_%7Bb_%7B0%7D%2C+b_%7B1%7D%7D+C%28b_%7B0%7D%2C+b_%7B1%7D%29+%3D+%5Cmin+%5Climits_%7B%7Bb_%7B0%7D%2C+b_%7B1%7D%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7Bi+%3D+1%7D%5E%7Bn%7D%28+y_%7Bi%7D+-+%28b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7D%2Ax_%7Bi%7D%29%5E%7B2%7D+%3D+%5Csum_%7Bi+%3D+1%7D%5E%7Bn%7D+%5Cepsilon_%7Bi%7D%5E%7B2%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cmin+%5Climits_%7Bb_%7B0%7D%2C+b_%7B1%7D%7D+C%28b_%7B0%7D%2C+b_%7B1%7D%29+%3D+%5Cmin+%5Climits_%7B%7Bb_%7B0%7D%2C+b_%7B1%7D%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7Bi+%3D+1%7D%5E%7Bn%7D%28+y_%7Bi%7D+-+%28b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7D%2Ax_%7Bi%7D%29%5E%7B2%7D+%3D+%5Csum_%7Bi+%3D+1%7D%5E%7Bn%7D+%5Cepsilon_%7Bi%7D%5E%7B2%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cmin+%5Climits_%7Bb_%7B0%7D%2C+b_%7B1%7D%7D+C%28b_%7B0%7D%2C+b_%7B1%7D%29+%3D+%5Cmin+%5Climits_%7B%7Bb_%7B0%7D%2C+b_%7B1%7D%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7Bi+%3D+1%7D%5E%7Bn%7D%28+y_%7Bi%7D+-+%28b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7D%2Ax_%7Bi%7D%29%5E%7B2%7D+%3D+%5Csum_%7Bi+%3D+1%7D%5E%7Bn%7D+%5Cepsilon_%7Bi%7D%5E%7B2%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"\u0026#92;min \u0026#92;limits_{b_{0}, b_{1}} C(b_{0}, b_{1}) = \u0026#92;min \u0026#92;limits_{{b_{0}, b_{1}}} \u0026#92;sum_{i = 1}^{n}( y_{i} - (b_{0} + b_{1}*x_{i})^{2} = \u0026#92;sum_{i = 1}^{n} \u0026#92;epsilon_{i}^{2}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ewhere \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=C%28a%2C+b%29\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=C%28a%2C+b%29\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=C%28a%2C+b%29\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"C(a, b)\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e is the cost function. In other words, we need to find \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=b_%7B0%7D%2C+b_%7B1%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=b_%7B0%7D%2C+b_%7B1%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=b_%7B0%7D%2C+b_%7B1%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"b_{0}, b_{1}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e such that \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7Dx_%7Bi%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7Dx_%7Bi%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=b_%7B0%7D+%2B+b_%7B1%7Dx_%7Bi%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"b_{0} + b_{1}x_{i}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e is close to \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"y\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e for all \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%28x_%7Bi%7D%2C+y_%7Bi%7D%29\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%28x_%7Bi%7D%2C+y_%7Bi%7D%29\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%28x_%7Bi%7D%2C+y_%7Bi%7D%29\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"(x_{i}, y_{i})\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e. That gives us the line with minimal distances between the data points (the line which best approximates the data).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCorrelation of \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=1\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=1\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=1\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"1\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e means that there is a strong relation between variables (the slope is increasing from left to right), while the correlation of \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=0\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=0\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=0\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"0\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e indicates that there is no relation between variables. The negative \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=-1\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=-1\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=-1\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"-1\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e correlation means negative association (the slope is decreasing from left to right).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe correlation coefficient is given by\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=r+%3D+%C2%A0%5Cfrac%7BCov%28x%2C+y%29%7D%7B%5Csqrt%7Bs_%7Bx%7D%5E%7B2%7D+s_%7By%7D%5E%7B2%7D%7D%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=r+%3D+%C2%A0%5Cfrac%7BCov%28x%2C+y%29%7D%7B%5Csqrt%7Bs_%7Bx%7D%5E%7B2%7D+s_%7By%7D%5E%7B2%7D%7D%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=r+%3D+%C2%A0%5Cfrac%7BCov%28x%2C+y%29%7D%7B%5Csqrt%7Bs_%7Bx%7D%5E%7B2%7D+s_%7By%7D%5E%7B2%7D%7D%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"r =  \u0026#92;frac{Cov(x, y)}{\u0026#92;sqrt{s_{x}^{2} s_{y}^{2}}}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ewhere\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Cov%28x%2C+y%29\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Cov%28x%2C+y%29\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Cov%28x%2C+y%29\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"Cov(x, y)\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e is the covariance of \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=x\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=x\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=x\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"x\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e and \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"y\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e defined as\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Cov%28x%2C+y%29+%3D%5Cfrac%7B+%5Csum%28X-%5Chat%7BX%7D%29%28Y-%5Chat%7BY%7D%29+%7D%7Bn+-+1%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Cov%28x%2C+y%29+%3D%5Cfrac%7B+%5Csum%28X-%5Chat%7BX%7D%29%28Y-%5Chat%7BY%7D%29+%7D%7Bn+-+1%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Cov%28x%2C+y%29+%3D%5Cfrac%7B+%5Csum%28X-%5Chat%7BX%7D%29%28Y-%5Chat%7BY%7D%29+%7D%7Bn+-+1%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"Cov(x, y) =\u0026#92;frac{ \u0026#92;sum(X-\u0026#92;hat{X})(Y-\u0026#92;hat{Y}) }{n - 1}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=n\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=n\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=n\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"n\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e is the number of data points in a file and\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=s_%7Bx%7D%5E%7B2%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=s_%7Bx%7D%5E%7B2%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=s_%7Bx%7D%5E%7B2%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"s_{x}^{2}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e and \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=s_%7By%7D%5E%7B2%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=s_%7By%7D%5E%7B2%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=s_%7By%7D%5E%7B2%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"s_{y}^{2}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e are the variances of \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=x\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=x\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=x\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"x\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e and \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=y\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"y\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e defined as\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=s_%7Bx%7D%5E%7B2%7D+%3D%5Cfrac%7B+%5Csum%28X-%5Chat%7BX%7D%29%5E%7B2%7D+%7D%7Bn+-+1%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=s_%7Bx%7D%5E%7B2%7D+%3D%5Cfrac%7B+%5Csum%28X-%5Chat%7BX%7D%29%5E%7B2%7D+%7D%7Bn+-+1%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=s_%7Bx%7D%5E%7B2%7D+%3D%5Cfrac%7B+%5Csum%28X-%5Chat%7BX%7D%29%5E%7B2%7D+%7D%7Bn+-+1%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"s_{x}^{2} =\u0026#92;frac{ \u0026#92;sum(X-\u0026#92;hat{X})^{2} }{n - 1}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=s_%7By%7D%5E%7B2%7D+%3D%5Cfrac%7B+%5Csum%28Y-%5Chat%7BY%7D%29%5E%7B2%7D+%7D%7Bn+-+1%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=s_%7By%7D%5E%7B2%7D+%3D%5Cfrac%7B+%5Csum%28Y-%5Chat%7BY%7D%29%5E%7B2%7D+%7D%7Bn+-+1%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=s_%7By%7D%5E%7B2%7D+%3D%5Cfrac%7B+%5Csum%28Y-%5Chat%7BY%7D%29%5E%7B2%7D+%7D%7Bn+-+1%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"s_{y}^{2} =\u0026#92;frac{ \u0026#92;sum(Y-\u0026#92;hat{Y})^{2} }{n - 1}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Chat%7BX%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Chat%7BX%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Chat%7BX%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"\u0026#92;hat{X}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e and \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Chat%7BY%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Chat%7BY%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Chat%7BY%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"\u0026#92;hat{Y}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e are sample means of \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=X\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=X\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=X\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"X\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e and \u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Y\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Y\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Y\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"Y\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe relationship between the linear regression line and the correlation coefficient is given by\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=b_%7B1%7D+%3D+r+%5Cfrac%7Bs_%7By%7D%7D%7Bs_%7Bx%7D%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\" srcset=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=b_%7B1%7D+%3D+r+%5Cfrac%7Bs_%7By%7D%7D%7Bs_%7Bx%7D%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002 1x, https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=b_%7B1%7D+%3D+r+%5Cfrac%7Bs_%7By%7D%7D%7Bs_%7Bx%7D%7D\u0026#038;bg=ffffff\u0026#038;fg=000\u0026#038;s=0\u0026#038;c=20201002\u0026#038;zoom=4.5 4x\" alt=\"b_{1} = r \u0026#92;frac{s_{y}}{s_{x}}\" class=\"latex\" /\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLet\u0026#8217;s try this in Python. First, we want to examine our data and see how scatterplot looks like. In Python we can achieve this with the following snippet of code:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003eimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\n\ndata = pd.read_csv('salary_data.csv')\n\nx = df.iloc[:, :-1].values\ny = df.iloc[:, 1].values\n\nplt.scatter(x, y, color='blue')\nplt.show()\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe important thing to notice here is that x is the matrix (the matrix of features of the independent variables(s), while y is a vector of the dependent variable).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis will give us the following figure:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" data-attachment-id=\"1018\" data-permalink=\"https://lucijagregov.com/2017/02/26/regression-linear/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-19-41-40/\" data-orig-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-19-41-40.png\" data-orig-size=\"1190,864\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026quot;aperture\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;credit\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;camera\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;caption\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;created_timestamp\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;copyright\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;focal_length\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;iso\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;shutter_speed\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;title\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;orientation\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Screen Shot 2017-03-08 at 19.41.40\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-19-41-40.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-19-41-40.png?w=529\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1018\" src=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-19-41-40.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2017-03-08 at 19.41.40\" width=\"1190\" height=\"864\" srcset=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-19-41-40.png 1190w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-19-41-40.png?w=150\u0026amp;h=109 150w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-19-41-40.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=218 300w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-19-41-40.png?w=768\u0026amp;h=558 768w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-19-41-40.png?w=1024\u0026amp;h=743 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1190px) 100vw, 1190px\" /\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe can see that the scatterplot clearly shows increasing of data and that we can pull the \u0026#8216;straight line\u0026#8217; through it to approximate it. Now let\u0026#8217;s calculate the correlation coefficient. We can use different correlation coefficients, for example, Pearson, Kendall, Spearman. For the purposes of this blog I will use the \u003ca href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pearson_correlation_coefficient#For_a_sample\"\u003ePearson correlation coefficient\u003c/a\u003e, which with Pandas library we can calculate easily:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003ecorr = df.corr(method='pearson')\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis gives us the correlation matrix between the columns:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"Apple-converted-space\"\u003e                        \u003c/span\u003eYearsExperience\u003cspan class=\"Apple-converted-space\"\u003e           \u003c/span\u003eSalary\u003c/span\u003e\n\n\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eYearsExperience \u003cspan class=\"Apple-converted-space\"\u003e          \u003c/span\u003e1.000000\u003cspan class=\"Apple-converted-space\"\u003e               \u003c/span\u003e0.978242\u003c/span\u003e\n\n\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eSalary\u003cspan class=\"Apple-converted-space\"\u003e                    \u003c/span\u003e0.978242\u003cspan class=\"Apple-converted-space\"\u003e               \u003c/span\u003e1.000000\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFrom this, we can see that correlation between variables is very high \u0026#8211; variables are highly associated. There are statistical methods which can be used to determine the statistical significance of the correlation coefficient, but I will talk more about that later.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSimilarly, as in \u003ca href=\"https://lucijagregov.wordpress.com/2016/12/30/multiple-linear-regression-in-python/\"\u003eMultiple Linear Regression in Python\u003c/a\u003e, one of the possibilities to do Linear Regression in Python follows ([1]). First, we need to split the dataset into the training set and the test set which is usually done using the 25-30%, 70-75% ratio. How to chose the data for the test and the training sets is another story and I will talk more about it in later posts. For now, I will do it randomly using 1/3 ratio with the sklearn library.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003efrom sklearn.cross_validation import train_test_split\nx_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size = 1/3.0, random_state = 0)\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNow we can fit the linear regression to the training set.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003efrom sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\nregressor = LinearRegression()\nregressor.fit(x_train, y_train)\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFinally, we can predict the results\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003ey_pred = regressor.predict(x_test)\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand visualize the training and test sets results:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003eplt.scatter(x_train, y_train, color = 'red')\nplt.plot(x_train, regressor.predict(x_train), color = 'blue')\nplt.title('Salary vs Experience (Training set)')\nplt.xlabel('Years of Experience')\nplt.ylabel('Salary')\nplt.show()\n\n\nplt.scatter(x_test, y_test, color = 'red')\nplt.plot(x_train, regressor.predict(x_train), color = 'blue')\nplt.title('Salary vs Experience (Test set)')\nplt.xlabel('Years of Experience')\nplt.ylabel('Salary')\nplt.show()\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe first plot gives us the following figure.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" data-attachment-id=\"1020\" data-permalink=\"https://lucijagregov.com/2017/02/26/regression-linear/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-34-29/\" data-orig-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-34-29.png\" data-orig-size=\"1234,956\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026quot;aperture\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;credit\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;camera\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;caption\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;created_timestamp\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;copyright\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;focal_length\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;iso\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;shutter_speed\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;title\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;orientation\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Screen Shot 2017-03-08 at 21.34.29\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-34-29.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-34-29.png?w=529\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1020\" src=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-34-29.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2017-03-08 at 21.34.29\" width=\"1234\" height=\"956\" srcset=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-34-29.png 1234w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-34-29.png?w=150\u0026amp;h=116 150w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-34-29.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=232 300w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-34-29.png?w=768\u0026amp;h=595 768w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-34-29.png?w=1024\u0026amp;h=793 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1234px) 100vw, 1234px\" /\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe blue line represents predicted values and the red dots represent real values. We used the training set to make our model \u0026#8216;learn\u0026#8217; about the data and now we can test how well out model can predict \u0026#8216;new\u0026#8217; data from the test set.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFrom the second plot, we get\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" data-attachment-id=\"1021\" data-permalink=\"https://lucijagregov.com/2017/02/26/regression-linear/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-36-05/\" data-orig-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-36-05.png\" data-orig-size=\"1230,932\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026quot;aperture\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;credit\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;camera\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;caption\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;created_timestamp\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;copyright\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;focal_length\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;iso\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;shutter_speed\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;title\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;orientation\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;0\u0026quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Screen Shot 2017-03-08 at 21.36.05\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-36-05.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-36-05.png?w=529\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1021\" src=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-36-05.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2017-03-08 at 21.36.05\" width=\"1230\" height=\"932\" srcset=\"https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-36-05.png 1230w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-36-05.png?w=150\u0026amp;h=114 150w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-36-05.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=227 300w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-36-05.png?w=768\u0026amp;h=582 768w, https://lucijagregov.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/screen-shot-2017-03-08-at-21-36-05.png?w=1024\u0026amp;h=776 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1230px) 100vw, 1230px\" /\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere the red dots are observation points of the test set and we can see that our model made some really good predictions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eResources:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.udemy.com/machinelearning/learn/v4/overview\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://www.udemy.com/machinelearning/learn/v4/overview\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.stat.yale.edu/Courses/1997-98/101/linreg.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttp://www.stat.yale.edu/Courses/1997-98/101/linreg.htm\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.coursera.org/learn/regression-models/lecture/CRfJS/linear-least-squares\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://www.coursera.org/learn/regression-models/lecture/CRfJS/linear-least-squares\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://galton.org/essays/1880-1889/galton-1886-jaigi-regression-stature.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttp://galton.org/essays/1880-1889/galton-1886-jaigi-regression-stature.pdf\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://sphweb.bumc.bu.edu/otlt/mph-modules/bs/bs704_multivariable/bs704_multivariable5.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttp://sphweb.bumc.bu.edu/otlt/mph-modules/bs/bs704_multivariable/bs704_multivariable5.html\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n",
